content:
To help agents quickly assess a customer, automatically search, link, or screen-pop records during active Messaging, Email-to-Case, or Voice conversations.

Agents need help with identifying the humans behind their customer interactions. Individual-Object Linking introduces a Search Individual flow action that associates contacts, leads, person accounts, or employees with an interaction.

To get started, Salesforce provides three flow templates that link individuals to interactions automatically. The basic premise of each flow template is that it takes an interaction record and runs a search for associated individuals based on an identifier.

Find Contact Associated with Voice Call uses the end userâ€™s phone number from the voice call record to find contacts associated with a voice call. Find Contact for Associated Case from Email-to-Case finds all contacts with email addresses that match the inbound email address that resulted in the case. Find Contact Associated with Messaging Session uses a search term or variable of your choice to find contacts associated with a messaging session.

The flow template for Find Contact Associated with Messaging Session lets you search leads, employees, and person accounts in addition to contacts. Building Individual-Object Linking into flows lets you map individuals to interactions in every channel.

To improve service and data quality, add a screen flow that guides agents to find and link callers to leads, contacts, or employees. To improve service quality, add a flow that finds contacts for cases created by Email-to-Case using the flow template Find Contact for Associated Case from Email-to-Case.
title: Individual-Object Linking for Service Cloud
